The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A youth allegedly snatched a gold chain and pendant worth Rs 40,000 from Usha Chowdhry, 54, on Wednesday morning in Salt Lake CG Block. Chowdhry, whose husband is a diamond merchant, was injured in the neck. Police said Chowdhry was out for her morning walk around 6.45am when the incident occurred. Local councillor Dilip Ghosh said cases of snatching had increased in the area in the past six months.    Taxi driver Arjun Roy, 25, who had hit a rickshaw at Sukantanagar on Tuesday, killing one and injuring three, was arrested at his Mukundapur home on Wednesday. Roy, who had fled after the mishap, was charged with rash and negligent driving and culpable homicide not amounting to murder. He was remanded in judicial custody till December 9.     State home secretary Ardhendu Sen said on Wednesday that surveillance and security measures would be stepped up in the state on Thursday, the first anniversary of Mumbai terror attacks. He, however, clarified that there were no intelligence inputs about the possibility of similar attacks in Bengal.     Two persons were killed in separate accidents in the city late on Tuesday. Tara Paswan, 65, was crushed by a truck in Jorabagan at 10.40pm.  olice said the vehicle hit him from behind while he was crossing the road. A police van rushed him to Calcutta Medical College, where he succumbed to his injuries. The driver fled without the truck.   round 12.10am, a 35-year-old motorcyclist was hit by an unknown vehicle on Asutosh Mukherjee Road. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead.     Pradip Bhunyia, 25, and Raju Das, 24, were arrested on Wednesday for allegedly lobbing crude bombs at a Trinamul Congress office in Bally on Tuesday night. An officer said the duo were caught by residents, beaten up and handed over to police. They were later admitted to TL Jaiswal Hospital.    Three persons were arrested on Wednesday for allegedly stealing taxis. Police said the trio stole a taxi on August 25 from Gariahat and another on September 9 from Ballygunge.  fter the taxi drivers lodged complaints, the cops picked up Sanjay from Chowbhaga in South 24-Parganas, Arunava Haldar from Garia and Raju Sarkar from Habra in North 24-Parganas. The taxis could not be recovered.  ops suspect they have been sold as scrap. An officer said Sanjay was the gang leader and the trio had confessed to their crime. A hunt is on for the other members of the gang.     A bag left behind by a passenger triggered a bomb scare at the international terminal of the airport on Wednesday morning.  ISF personnel, who noticed the bag around 11am, alerted the bomb squad. The bag was found to contain clothes and a camera and was handed over to the airport authorities.  antosh Ghosh, who had arrived from Bangkok in a Jet Airways flight, later reclaimed his bag.     A white Tata Sumo Victa (WB 23B 5625) was stolen from Beleghata Main Road on Tuesday.                                                                                                                                                  
